The paper discusses hardware security and protection of intellectual property (IP) in chip design, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of emerging devices for low-power and inexact computing, which can be categorized under embedded systems (cs.ET) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper discusses the use of logic locking and camouflaging techniques for IP protection, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic computing and its resilience against Boolean satisfiability (SAT) attacks, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
